Name: lineWidth

Details:

Categories: Library

Syntax:

Types:

Function: 
# `FProperty lineWidth(num w)`
# `FProperty lineWidth(computedNum cw)`

Synopsis:

Description: Set the width of lines and borders of figures to `w`.
The width value may also be computed by a callback `cw`.

Examples:
<figure lw1.png>
b1 = box([size(50), lineWidth(1)]);
b2 = box([size(50), lineWidth(2)]);
b3 = box([size(50), lineWidth(3)]);
b4 = box([size(50), lineWidth(4)]);
boxes = [b1, b2, b3, b4];
render(hcat(boxes));
</figure>
